SIMPLE: self-conscious
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Self-conscious
<hw>Self`-con"scious</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Conscious of one's acts or state as belonging to, or originating
in, one's self.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧My <xex>self-conscious</xex> worth.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Conscious of one's self as an object of the
observation of others; <as>as, the speaker was too
<ex>self-conscious</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Self-consciousness</ent>⟦br⟧
